Function select: (-> Atom %Undefined%) HE-extended committed choice over nondeterministic results. The primary form (select results) returns the first non-empty result encountered under the active traversal policy. The extended forms (select k results), (select (search-policy lane) results), and (select k (search-policy lane) results) expose bounded selection and explicit search-lane choice.
Parameters:
  Atom Result expression to evaluate
Return: (type %Undefined%) Selected result, or a bounded packet in the two-argument extended form
Function collect: (-> Atom Expression) Compatibility collector over nondeterministic results. Evaluates the result fan-out, packages all non-empty results into one expression, and preserves the current traversal order. Prefer collapse in new code when you do not need explicit search-policy or result-order control. The policy form (collect (search-policy lane) results) keeps the lane/order choice explicit.
Parameters:
  Atom Result expression to evaluate
Return: (type Expression) Collected expression of surviving results in current traversal order
Function once: (-> Atom %Undefined%) Compatibility alias for select. Prefer select in new code. The policy form (once (search-policy lane) results) is supported for legacy call sites that still want explicit search-lane choice.
Parameters:
  Atom Result expression to evaluate
Return: (type %Undefined%) First non-empty result encountered under the active traversal policy
Function search-policy: (-> Atom Atom) Search-policy literal constructor for explicit controlled-search calls. The current native CeTTa lane is recursive-dependent-proof, and it supports result-order control through (search-policy recursive-dependent-proof), (search-policy recursive-dependent-proof (order reverse)), (search-policy recursive-dependent-proof (order lex)), and (search-policy recursive-dependent-proof (order shortlex)). The lex mode orders results by canonical rendered-atom bytes. The shortlex mode orders results by canonical rendered-atom length first, then bytewise lexical order. ATP and solver lanes are named here for future explicit oracle work, but are not executed by the native evaluator yet.
Parameters:
  Atom Search lane name such as recursive-dependent-proof
Return: (type Atom) Opaque policy atom consumed by select, fold, fold-by-key, collect, or once
